codex
Two material risks are emerging: supplied LP validation does not read or compare `warehouse_id` (despite it being non-null in the schema), and genealogy assigns the WO’s entire net parent consumption to every output LP created for that WO, which double-counts across partial/multiple outputs. I’m validating these against callers and tests, and checking the explicit canonical-ownership grep.
exec
